## Next Steps

**Build order — 60-minute timeline:**

### [0–5 min] HTML scaffold
One file. Dark background, monospace font. Elements you need:
- `#api-key-screen` — password input + Start button
- `#game-screen` (hidden) — code display, line numbers, timer bar, round counter
- `#result-screen` (hidden) — final score, Play Again button

### [5–20 min] Claude API call

```javascript
async function fetchRound() {
  const prompt = `Generate a short (8-12 line) JavaScript code snippet with EXACTLY ONE bug.
Return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown fences, no preamble):
{"code": "line1\\nline2\\n...", "bugLine": N, "explanation": "one sentence"}
Rules: bugLine is 1-indexed. Bug must NOT be on line 1.
Bug types: off-by-one, wrong operator, wrong variable name, missing negation.
Make it subtle but findable in 15 seconds.`;

  try {
    const res = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'x-api-key': apiKey,
        'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01',
        'content-type': 'application/json',
        'anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access': 'true'
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        model: 'claude-haiku-4-5-20251001',   // use full versioned slug
        max_tokens: 512,
        messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }]
      })
    });
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`API error ${res.status}`);
    const data = await res.json();
    // Strip markdown fences Claude sometimes adds despite instructions
    const raw = data.content[0].text.replace(/```json?\n?|\n?```/g, '').trim();
    return JSON.parse(raw);
  } catch (err) {
    showError(err.message || 'Network error — check your API key and connection');
    return null;   // caller checks for null and skips the round
  }
}
```

**Model slug:** `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`. Using the wrong slug produces a silent 404 on every round.

**CORS note:** The `anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access: true` header must be
exact (lowercase). GitHub Pages does not set a restrictive CSP, so direct browser
calls work fine there.

**Rate limit safety:** Add a 1-second delay between rounds if you hit 429s.
10 rounds = well within free tier limits.

### [20–35 min] Game loop

State machine: `idle → loading → playing → reveal → next round → end`.

```javascript
let timeRemaining = 15;
let timerInterval;

async function startRound() {
  // Show a "Loading…" placeholder while waiting for the API
  document.getElementById('code-display').textContent = 'Loading…';

  const round = await fetchRound();
  if (!round) return;  // fetchRound showed an error; don't advance

  // renderCode: split on \n, produce <div class="code-line" style="white-space:pre">
  // with a <span class="ln">N </span> prefix for the line number
  renderCode(round.code);

  timeRemaining = 15;
  timerInterval = setInterval(() => {
    timeRemaining--;
    updateTimerBar(timeRemaining);       // CSS width: (timeRemaining/15)*100%
    if (timeRemaining <= 0) onTimeout(round);
  }, 1000);

  document.querySelectorAll('.code-line').forEach((el, i) => {
    el.onclick = () => onGuess(i + 1, round);
  });
}

function onGuess(clicked, round) {
  clearInterval(timerInterval);
  const correct = clicked === round.bugLine;
  // highlight: add class .correct (green bg) to the correct line,
  //            add class .wrong (red bg) to the clicked line if wrong
  document.querySelectorAll('.code-line')[round.bugLine - 1].classList.add('correct');
  if (!correct) document.querySelectorAll('.code-line')[clicked - 1].classList.add('wrong');
  if (correct) score += 100 + Math.floor(timeRemaining);
  showExplanation(round.explanation);
  setTimeout(() => nextRound(), 1400);
}

function onTimeout(round) {
  // Timeout = no points, reveal correct line, same visual as wrong guess
  clearInterval(timerInterval);
  document.querySelectorAll('.code-line')[round.bugLine - 1].classList.add('correct');
  showExplanation(`Time's up! Bug was: ${round.explanation}`);
  setTimeout(() => nextRound(), 1400);
}
```

**Round counter and Play Again:**
```javascript
let currentRound = 0;
const ROUNDS = 10; // set to 3 during development

function nextRound() {
  currentRound++;
  if (currentRound >= ROUNDS) return showEndScreen();
  startRound();
}

function resetGame() {
  score = 0; currentRound = 0;
  document.querySelectorAll('.code-line').forEach(el => el.className = 'code-line');
  startRound();
}
```

**On null round** (API error mid-game): `startRound` returns early after showing the error
message. The game stalls gracefully rather than crashing — the player can reload.

**Screen transitions:** toggle `display:none` / `display:block` on the three screen divs.
Timer bar HTML: `<div id="timer-bar" style="height:6px;background:#0f0;width:100%;transition:width 1s linear"></div>`

**CORS fallback:** if the API call fails in the browser, serve the file via
`python3 -m http.server` locally or confirm `anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access:true`
is still supported. The hardcoded API key approach avoids all CORS issues for the demo.

### [35–45 min] Score + end screen

After round 10:
```
You found N/10 bugs.
Score: X points
[Play Again]
```

Score formula: **+100 per correct answer + floor(seconds remaining) as bonus points**.

### [45–60 min] Polish

- Animated timer bar: CSS `transition: width 1s linear` on a `<div>` driven by the
  `setInterval` counter — update width to `(timeRemaining/15)*100%` each tick.
- Correct answer reveal: flash correct line green, show explanation below the code for 1.4s.
- Wrong answer: flash red on clicked line, then reveal correct line in green.
- Tweak the prompt if bugs are consistently too easy or too hard after 2–3 test runs.
- **Dev shortcut:** Set `const ROUNDS = 3` during development; restore to 10 before demo.
  Full 10-round playthroughs take 3–5 min each — too slow for tight iteration loops.

